        "title": "Python for (Almost) Everything",
        "description": "Join us at Downtown TREX as we celebrate the 1 year anniversary of PySTL! In this mini conference, we will bring in speakers from industry, researchers, and students to talk about the various ways Python is used. We will cover a broad array of topics such as Web Development, Geospatial, and AI.\n\n**Schedule of Events:**\nTBD\n\n**Partners and Sponsors**\nWe are sponsored by\n\n* [Python Software Foundation](https://www.python.org/psf/community-partners/#psf-community-partners)\n* [Manning Publishing](https://www.manning.com/)\n\nWe partner with\n\n* [St. Louis Code and Coffee](https://www.meetup.com/code-and-coffee-st-louis/),\n* [Bourbon Friday](https://www.meetup.com/bourbonfridays/)\n* [Tech Lunch STL](https://www.heylo.com/g/c45b7312-6acc-4b4f-bc31-a0d92fb74b59)\n* [PyData St. Louis](https://www.meetup.com/pydata-st-louis/)",
